Current Strategy

This is what I am invested in currently, but please note that what I invest in changes frequently, often multiple times per week, so please note the "last updated" line above. The amount you may invest with for each Symphony and how much risk you want to take is up to you. Especially look at the Volatility, Max Drawdown, and other factors on each Symphony's linked statistical pages before investing in any of the listed strategies, regardless of their estimated annual returns. I am not a certified financial advisor, all investments are made at your own risk. It is also very important to check and make sure that the title you see for each Symphony on this page matches the Symphony that you actually invest in when clicking the "Invest" link. If they do not match, do NOT invest in the strategy as that means it has changed since I ran the backtests and simulations.

The Risk Bar to the left of each Symphony is calculated as follows, weighting heavily negative high volatility, high max drawdown, and backtest years since 2000, while favorably weighting Gain/Pain Ratio and the Profit Factor: -(0.6*-Volatility) - (0.6*-MaxD) - (0.25*-DailyVaR) + (0.55*GPRatio) + (0.8*ProfitF) + (0.55*Backtest) = Risk (from 0% to 100%).
For example, looking at the Wooden ARKK Machine: -(0.6*-80.92)-(0.6*-15.70)-(0.25*-6.91)-(0.55*1.32)-(0.8*2.32)+(0.55*22) = 0.692175, putting it at a "high-risk" level.
